	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          'n' is the value to convert to a string in itob().&nbsp; It's also the value in which to count all the 1 bits in bitcount(). <br>  <br> It's not safe to assume that an 'int' is 32 bits wide.&nbsp; It's not even safe to assume that it is as least 32 bits wide.&nbsp; The only guarantees you have about an int are that (1) it's at least 16 bits wide; (2) it's at least as wide as a 'short'; and (3) it's no longer than a 'long'. <br>  <br>  
          
